text: St. Antony's College is one of the colleges of the University of Oxford. It was founded in 1950 and received a Royal Charter in 1953. It claims to be the most cosmopolitan of the University's seven graduate colleges."Welcome to St. Antony's", St. Antony's College Website ==References== Category:1950 establishments in Europe Category:1950s establishments in England Category:Colleges of the University of Oxford
